  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you’re after a relaxed luxury hotel in the Dolomites, then look no further than Hotel Sassongher. The Pescosta family have created a wonderful place where you’ll feel instantly welcome – it’s the reason lots of people return year after year. The décor is a mix of modern and Alpine. You’ll love coming back here at the end of the day and chilling out in the spacious rooms. They’ve all got private balconies that either look out over the town or have incredible mountain views depending on which category you choose.</p>
<p>The location’s fantastic with the village centre just a five-minute walk away where you can jump on the Piz La Ila gondola and ski down the Sellaronda. The hotel puts on a free shuttle any time you need it between 8am and 8pm that’ll drop you off at the centre of the lift, or bring you back at the end of the day. There’s a good reason to drag yourself away from the slopes. The hotel’s spa is the perfect place to soothe your legs. The infrared sauna eases muscle tension or you can just take a leisurely swim in the pool. Personally, we prefer heading for the rooftop Jacuzzi and sauna. There’s nothing quite like relaxing under the shadow of the snowy Mount Sassongher.</p>
<p>You’re in for a real treat when it comes to food here. Wake up to a healthy breakfast that runs til late for when you need a lie in. Dinner is a celebration of South Tyrolean cuisine that you can wash down with a glass of local wine. It’ll become the highlight of your day.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 3 hours from Innsbruck airport.</p>]]></description>
